---
const nodes=['CEO B Core','Market Habitat','Life Habitat','Knowledge Core','Agent Habitat','Archive','Founder Page','Bookmark Intake','Final Checklist'];
---
<html lang="en"><head><title>Vision Map — Pickaxe Capital</title><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" /><style>body{margin:0;background:#04060b;color:white;font-family:Inter,system-ui}.map{min-height:100vh;padding:38px;background:radial-gradient(circle at 50% 25%,rgba(38,115,255,.22),transparent 38%),#04060b}h1{font-size:44px;margin:0}.nodes{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:18px;margin-top:30px}.node{border:1px solid rgba(247,184,75,.25);background:linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(12,20,38,.88),rgba(4,7,13,.88));border-radius:22px;padding:24px;min-height:150px;position:relative;overflow:hidden}.node:before{content:"";position:absolute;inset:auto -30% -45% -30%;height:90%;background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(168,85,247,.28),transparent 60%)}.node b{color:#f7b84b;font-size:22px}.node p{color:#aab6c9;line-height:1.55}@media(max-width:800px){.nodes{grid-template-columns:1fr}}</style></head><body><main class="map"><h1>VISION MAP</h1><p>One clean ecosystem map. CEO B connects every habitat, but each page stays separate.</p><section class="nodes">{nodes.map((n,i)=><article class="node"><b>{String(i+1).padStart(2,'0')} — {n}</b><p>{n==='CEO B Core'?'Final decisions, personal preference memory, and command routing.':'Connected module with its own page, checklist, logs, and archive flow.'}</p></article>)}</section></main></body></html>
